author: Ruth Brown
title: Gator shows off dinner on stroll through golf course | New York Post
text:
Score!
A Florida gator landed a hearty meal — a massive fish — and then was caught on tape casually strolling through a golf course with it in his mouth Thursday afternoon.
Norma Respess was at the 10th hole at the Seven Springs Golf and Country Club in Trinity when the gator suddenly strolled across the course with dinner in its jaws, before slipping into a water hazard, she told a local ABC affiliate .
Her sister-in-law, Phyllis Respess, bolted, but Norma whipped out her phone and caught the whole thing on camera.
“That’s amazing I’ve never seen that before!” she says in the footage. “Wow, what a sight — he’s holding onto that fish! Amazing!”
